Role description This position is a leadership position responsible for complete warehouse deliverables & service center operation such that there is continuous improvement in efficiency, quality & customer success. The position holder manage associated service market contracts and also take the role of host manager for Service Market Logistics, UD Trucks in South Africa This with strong focus on developing people, processes, tools, working environment and an inclusive culture that can meet or exceed current and future customers demands and legislation within UD Trucks Standards and also Industry benchmarks The position will report to Director, Overseas Operations - Service Market Logistics, UD Trucks Role Responsibilities Accountability and optimization of performance for all warehouse operational processes related to PDC Drive optimization in Warehouse Operations with end2end Supply Chain Value Manage operational internal interfaces and external customer demands having efficient communication and relationships to ensure needs of our organization and customers are met. Develop, recommend and implement improvements in the internal materials handling and administrative processes to improve quality, customer service, lead-time, productivity and cost efficiency. Compliance to Internal/ External Audits without any non- conformance and ensuring adherence to systems and processes Develop an engaged and inclusive organization through the insistence on and the application of the UD Trucks Values Manage the investigations of dealer discrepancy claims and nil picks, with actionable recommendations on findings, securing a reduction in these occurrence\u2019s Drive all Master Plan related projects and activities to reach the desired organization, and continuously strive for increased performance Support cost deployment activities to further strengthen and rollout our Lean Management concept within SML South Africa. Manage the cross-functional activities between different teams SML South Africa, UDT Market company and other stake holders internal and external Handle Environment and Security management Follow up DC expenses and assets mangement Set the rules for stocktaking for DC South Africa. To ensure entire inbound, outbound and warehousing procedures and routines are fulfilled. Perform capacity planning. Achieves financial objectives by preparing an annual budget, scheduling expenditures, analyzing variances and initiating corrective actions. Ensure that we comply with ISO 9001(Quality):14000(Environment):18001(OHSAS) Required knowledge and Experience 3 year Management Degree / Diploma Supply Chain and Logistics Diploma The Role Holder need to have extensive experience in Logistics. The Role Holder must have experience with Operational processes and Supply Chain processes (aftermarket) as well as a strong understanding of business challenges in an international environment. The Role Holder is skilled in coaching and developing Team Leaders and Members having a very good interpersonal relations and organizational development mindset. The Role Holder must have hands on project management experience as leader or senior team member. The Role Holder has cross functional mindset and is a strong communicator having good influencing skills, also able to create trusting relationships in spite of cultural differences and geographical distance The Role Holder has strong interpersonal skills with a high degree of \u2018flexibility\u2019, including the ability to network effectively across the Company and to build enduring relationships across functional areas and geographical areas. The Role Holder has significant change management experience and demonstrated ability to set demanding targets and to motivate teams and individuals to deliver outside their comfort zones, whilst further developing an excellent working climate and atmosphere in alignment with the UD Trucks Values and the Code of Conduct. Key Competencies Ability to perform complex logistic analysis Business oriented Excellent team player and communicator High numerical skills Self-motivated Lateral Thinking Holistic view, ability to locate and solve problems Demonstrate computer skills with high proficiency in MS office applications Strong written, verbal and communication skills The Volvo Group is one of the world\u2019s leading manufacturers of trucks, buses, construction equipment and marine and industrial engines under the leading brands Volvo, Renault Trucks, Mack, UD Trucks, Eicher, SDLG, Terex Trucks, Prevost, Nova Bus, UD Bus, Sunwin Bus and Volvo Penta. UD Trucks and JVs is an international commercial vehicle solutions provider based and headquartered in Japan. UD Trucks and JVs develop, produce and sell a wide range of heavy, medium and light-duty vehicles, supporting smart logistics solutions across 60 countries. Our trucks go the extra distance, giving our customers extra fuel mileage and uptime. Our 8,000 smart, modern and diversified colleagues work with passion, trust and change to stay ahead for performance. We will always go the extra mile for our customers and business partners. About us The Volvo Group drives prosperity through transport solutions, offering trucks, buses, construction equipment, power solutions for marine and industrial applications, financing and services that increase our customers\u2019 uptime and productivity. Founded in 1927, the Volvo Group is committed to shaping the future landscape of sustainable transport and infrastructure solutions. Countless career opportunities are offered across the group\u2019s leading brands - Volvo, Volvo Penta, UD Trucks, Terex Trucks, SDLG, Renault Trucks, Prevost, Nova Bus, Mack, Eicher, Dongfeng Trucks and Arquus. UD Trucks is an international commercial vehicle solutions provider based and headquartered in Japan. UD Trucks develop, produce and sell a wide range of heavy, medium and light-duty vehicles, supporting smart logistics solutions across 60 countries. Our trucks g